{
  "name": "RPlog_In_Mourning",
  "title": "In Mourning",
  "summary": "In the moonlit Caamasi Gardens of Ord Mantell, the battered New Republic pilot Raxis L'ygr, freshly shot down and patched up, shares a bench-side conversation with the racer Shael Winters, who has wandered in to clear her head after a trial. The two trade war stories -- Raxis recounting his repeated defeats at the hands of the Imperial ace Krieg, Shael her own near-death capture by the Empire -- and Raxis confides his weary, humanizing view that the enemy too have families and that war is only easy on the dead. He reveals his affection for Serenella and asks Shael to look after her, swearing her to secrecy about his sympathy for Imperial pilots. As Raxis grows dizzy from his pain medication, Shael insists on walking him back, and the pair exchange names and easy banter about their flying upbringings on the way to the medical center. They part at the hospital, where a stern Mon Calamari nurse collects Raxis, and Shael heads back to the starport for a morning run.",
